## Content Strategy

### The Mix

- **70% Craft & Expertise** — visual breakdowns, design decisions, opinions on UI trends, process reveals, component work. This is what builds a reputation in the design community and with hirers.
- **15% Personal / Behind the screen** — career moments, the ugly draft that became a great design, honest observations about the work. Humanizes without dominating.
- **15% Conversion** — job-search posts, client offers, portfolio drops. Direct asks, done right.

### Post Types

| Type | Job | Frequency |
|------|-----|-----------|
| **Authority** | Show craft and point of view | 2 of every 3 posts |
| **Visibility** | Reach new people with story or relatable take | 1 of every 3 posts |
| **Conversion** | Direct ask — job or client | Max 1× per 2 weeks |

UI designers should lean on visuals whenever possible. A great screenshot with 3 lines of context often beats 300 words.

