## Profile Optimization

Before any content strategy, make sure visitors convert:

**Headline:** Not just a title. What you make + for what context + what it does.
Example: *"UI Designer · Consumer Apps & SaaS · Interfaces people actually enjoy using"*

**Banner:** Show work. A polished screenshot, a component grid, a color system — something that proves taste immediately.

**About:** First person. Short. Who you are → what you make → what you're after. One visual reference or metric if possible. End with a CTA.

**Featured:** Best project (screenshot + 1-line outcome), portfolio link, or best-performing post.

**Experience:** One visual or metric outcome per role. "Redesigned the onboarding flow" is weak. "Redesigned onboarding — signup completion went from 54% to 71%" is strong.

